    <item>
      <title>Overview</title>
      <link>/tutorial/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Sep 2018 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/tutorial/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This feature can be used for publishing content such as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project or software documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Online courses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tutorials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The parent folder may be renamed, for example, to &lt;code&gt;docs&lt;/code&gt; for project documentation or &lt;code&gt;course&lt;/code&gt; for creating an online course.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To disable this feature, either delete the parent folder, or set &lt;code&gt;draft = true&lt;/code&gt; in the front matter of all its pages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After renaming or deleting the parent folder, you may wish to update any &lt;code&gt;[[menu.main]]&lt;/code&gt; menu links to it in the &lt;code&gt;config.toml&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
